This paper deals with mathematical characterization and fast algorithms for permutations used in signal processing and communication systems. It involves topics such as interleavers, fast Fourier transforms, and error correction codes, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses parallelization techniques, which are relevant to the systems and control (cs.SI) sub-category. The use of mathematical functions and closed-form expressions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the computer algebra (cs.AR) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes hardware-efficient architectures, which are relevant to the modeling and simulation (cs.MS) sub-category.
